2366:The system prompt does most of the relationship-quality and scope-discipline work. Three things specifically: the explicit out-of-scope list with named recipe pathways for each adjacent topic (so the LLM defers cleanly when a patient asks about a benefits question rather than guessing), the citation requirement (which prevents the LLM from freestyling coordination assertions from its parametric memory), and the deference clause (which catches the cases that look like coordination but cross into clinical judgment).
